Description: A small pottery beaker of coarse siltware. The surface is discoloured, possibly by burning. Part of the rim is missing. There is a roughly flat string-cut base.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Findspot 54, dry well south of the "Qasr"
Curator's comments: Information regarding findspot only in Museum register and on plate xxxv, 60. In the text (Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 67 § 61), Petrie mentions only, for Findspot 54, "large quantities of 54 and 80", but this 54 might be a typographic error due to the findspot number itself, and might read 60 instead..
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 64, 67 § 61, pl. xxxv, 60)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.103, p.134, p.191, pl.33)
